The body of a 10-year-old girl who went missing last Friday was found Tuesay in Mwingi West. The naked body, which was dumped near Itoloni Secondary School in Mwingi West, had some parts missing. According to Itoloni chief Freconah Kithikii, the girls leg and hand had been chopped off. Part of the head had also been skinned. Villagers who had been mobilised to look for the girl stumbled on the body at 11am. &quot;We are told that she got lost on Friday after separating with other children while they were coming from a nearby shopping centre but the heartless manner in which she was killed has shocked everybody,&quot; said Kithikii. She said the Class Four pupil live with her grandmother.